FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1773936670
OL,3,CBank keeps interest rates on hold and
OL,4,Cwarns the war will push up inflation
OL,6,FThis morning, the price of UK natural
OL,7,Fgas - used by OFGEM to calculate the
OL,8,Fcap on domestic energy bills - jumped
OL,9,Fby 15%, following the bombing of the
OL,10,Fworld's largest LNG plant in Qatar.
OL,12,FOil has jumped to over $116 a barrel.
OL,13,FOn February 27, before the first
OL,14,Fmissile was fired at Iran, it was
OL,15,Ftrading at $72.
OL,17,FAn energy price shock of unknowable
OL,18,Fscale is underway, and the first waves
OL,19,Fhave already reached our shores.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1773936670
OL,3,CBank keeps interest rates on hold and
OL,4,Cwarns the war will push up inflation
OL,6,FAt the pumps, the price of petrol has
OL,7,Frisen by 10 pence a litre, diesel is
OL,8,Fup 20 pence - the price of both will
OL,9,Fclimb further in the days ahead.
OL,11,FIt's not clear how long the conflict
OL,12,Fwill last, but the Bank notes that the
OL,13,Fsupply of oil and gas from the Gulf
OL,14,F"would take time to recover" even if
OL,15,Fit ends in short order.
OL,17,FThe targeting of energy infrastructure
OL,18,Fincreases the risk of prolonged
OL,19,Fdisruption.
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1773936670
OL,3,CBank keeps interest rates on hold and
OL,4,Cwarns the war will push up inflation
OL,6,F"War in the Middle East has pushed up
OL,7,Fglobal energy prices. You can already
OL,8,Fsee that at the petrol pump scam; if
OL,9,Fit lasts, it will feed into higher
OL,10,Fhousehold energy bills later in the
OL,11,Fyear," Andrew Bailey said. "The best
OL,12,Fway to tackle this at the source is by
OL,13,Freopening energy supply lines."
OL,15,FBefore the war, prices in the UK were
OL,16,Fstabilising. The Bank was forecasting
OL,17,Fthe headline annual rate of inflation
OL,18,Fwould fade to the 2% target by June
OL,19,Fand remain there.
OL,21,FThat forecast has been ditched.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@FO]sD@\OUuD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1773936670
OL,3,CBank keeps interest rates on hold and
OL,4,Cwarns the war will push up inflation
OL,6,FThe Bank calculates that if energy
OL,7,Fprices remain elevated, inflation will
OL,8,Frise by one percentage point.
OL,10,FEven that calculation, made on Monday
OL,11,F16th, now looks out of date given that
OL,12,Fenergy prices have since risen higher.
OL,14,FWho knows what will happen next?
OL,16,FThe Bank points out that prices are
OL,17,Frising because the supply of energy
OL,18,Fhas been disrupted, not because demand
OL,19,Fin the economy is too strong.
OL,21,FThat distinction is crucial.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1773936670
OL,3,CBank keeps interest rates on hold and
OL,4,Cwarns the war will push up inflation
OL,6,FHigher interest rates can't unblock
OL,7,Fthe Strait of Hormuz. They can't end
OL,8,Fthe war or revive gas production.
OL,10,FThey won't address the root cause of
OL,11,Fthe problem, but they would increase
OL,12,Fthe cost of borrowing and subdue
OL,13,Fspending and investment, further
OL,14,Fweakening economic growth.
OL,16,FEnergy prices have spiked; they could
OL,17,Fstabilise or sharply reverse if the
OL,18,Fconflict ends soon.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1773936670
OL,3,CBank keeps interest rates on hold and
OL,4,Cwarns the war will push up inflation
OL,6,FHowever, the Bank will feel pressure
OL,7,Fto intervene if it seems evidence of
OL,8,Fworkers demanding and being awarded
OL,9,Fhigher pay or businesses broadly
OL,10,Fincreasing their prices.
OL,12,FThe Bank says it "stands ready to act
OL,13,Fas necessary to ensure that CPI
OL,14,Finflation remains on track to meet the
OL,15,F2% target in the medium term."
OL,17,FWho knows where we'll be when the MPC
OL,18,Fnext meets in six weeks? The next move
OL,19,Fcould be up as well as down.
OL,26,@tD@ROUwD@^O]
